* UH-OH

02:06.090 --> 02:07.648
* UH-OH

02:07.690 --> 02:10.887
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

02:10.930 --> 02:12.795
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

02:12.830 --> 02:15.025
COMMISSIONER.

02:15.060 --> 02:16.049
[ DOG BARKING ]

02:16.100 --> 02:17.465
DID NOT EXPECT
TO SEE YOU THIS M--

02:17.500 --> 02:20.196
[ CHUCKLES ]
THIS MORNING...OR ANY MORNING.

02:20.240 --> 02:22.800
RELAX. [ SIGHS ]

02:22.840 --> 02:24.068
YOU KNOW,
WE GO WAY BACK.

02:24.110 --> 02:25.805
I'VE SEEN YOU
IN YOUR SKIWIES BEFORE.

02:25.840 --> 02:28.331
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
YEAH.

02:28.380 --> 02:30.075
I HEARD THAT YOU TURNED IN
YOUR BADGE YESTERDAY.

02:30.110 --> 02:31.338
UH, YEAH, YEAH,
YOU HEARD RIGHT.

02:31.380 --> 02:34.076
I MEAN, DID I --
DID I HAVE A CHOICE?

02:34.120 --> 02:36.213
WELL,
YOU ALWAYS GOT A CHOICE.

02:36.250 --> 02:38.514
YOU CAN STAY AND FIGHT IT,
YOU KNOW, DIG IN YOUR HEELS,

02:38.550 --> 02:40.051
MAYBE PROVE
YOU'RE INNOCENT.

02:40.090 --> 02:41.489
AND I KNOW
YOU HAD NOTHING TO DO

02:41.520 --> 02:43.329
WITH THE BOMBING
IN THE EVIDENCE ROOM.

02:43.360 --> 02:46.193
TED MCDONALD PLANTED A BOMB,
END OF STORY.

02:46.230 --> 02:48.357
YEAH, WELL, I THOUGHT YOU SAID
I HAD A CHOICE.

02:48.400 --> 02:51.096
THIS MORNING, I WAS TALKING
TO A FRIEND OF MINE --

02:51.130 --> 02:54.566
WENDELL FRANKS,
C.E.O. OF LAND-TECH ENTERPRISES.

02:54.600 --> 02:57.160
HE'S LOOKING
FOR A NEW HEAD OF SECURITY.

02:57.210 --> 02:58.666
IT PAYS ALMOST DOUBLE
WHAT YOU GET AT 15.

02:58.710 --> 03:01.770
THERE ARE BENEFITS,
FLEXIBLE HOURS.

03:01.810 --> 03:04.244
YOU CAN SPEND SOME MORE TIME
WITH THAT DAUGHTER OF YOURS,

03:04.280 --> 03:06.248
YOU KNOW, MAYBE PAY OFF
SOME OF THOSE BILLS.

03:06.280 --> 03:10.341
YEAH. AND, UH,
IN EXCHANGE FOR WHAT?

03:10.390 --> 03:12.483
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
PLAY BALL.

03:12.520 --> 03:16.957
YOU RETIRE YOUR BADGE,
YOU KNOW, WALK AWAY QUIETLY.

03:16.990 --> 03:18.287
I CAN DEEP-SIX
THE INVESTIGATION,

03:18.330 --> 03:19.922
BUT YOU CAN'T BE AROUND
WHILE I DO IT.

03:19.960 --> 03:22.667
AND IF I SAY,
"NO, THANK YOU"?

03:22.700 --> 03:24.622
YOU KNOW
HOW THIS IS GONNA GO.

03:24.670 --> 03:27.639
I.A. IS GONNA PICK
YOUR LIFE APART PIECE BY PIECE.

03:27.670 --> 03:29.729
AND EVEN
IF YOU BEAT THE BOMBING,

03:29.770 --> 03:31.465
THEY'RE GONNA FIND
SOMETHING ELSE.

03:31.510 --> 03:34.001
SOUNDS A BIT LIKE A THREAT,
MY FRIEND.

03:34.040 --> 03:35.803
IT'S A FACT.

03:35.840 --> 03:39.241
LISTEN, WHY DON'T YOU GO HAVE
YOUR COFFEE, THINK IT OVER?

03:39.280 --> 03:42.511
GET BACK TO ME
REAL SOON

03:42.550 --> 03:45.849
'CAUSE I CAN ONLY STALL
FOR SO LONG, OKAY?

03:45.890 --> 03:47.881
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

03:52.430 --> 03:55.752
Sam:
I'M NOT GOING IN.

03:55.800 --> 03:59.292
I GET IT. YESTERDAY
FREAKED ME OUT, TOO, YOU KNOW?

03:59.340 --> 04:02.434
FINALLY FINDING CHRIS KLEM
AND THEN HIM JUST

04:02.470 --> 04:04.700
POINTING THE FINGER BACK
AT OLIVER -- THAT SUCKED.

04:04.740 --> 04:07.573
WE BOTH KNOW OLIVER
DIDN'T DO ANYTHING, RIGHT?

04:07.610 --> 04:09.771
BUT THERE'S ALL THIS EVIDENCE
THAT SAYS THAT HE DID.

04:09.810 --> 04:13.849
HE WAS SET UP
BY COMMISSIONER SANTANA.

04:13.880 --> 04:16.348
WHAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND
IS WHY HE ROLLED OVER SO EASILY.

04:16.390 --> 04:18.642
HAVE YOU EVER KNOWN HIM
TO WALK AWAY FROM A FIGHT?

04:18.690 --> 04:20.783
NO.

04:20.820 --> 04:22.651
SO, I THINK THERE'S SOMETHING
HE'S NOT TELLING US.

04:22.690 --> 04:23.987
I WANT TO FIND OUT
WHAT IT IS.

04:24.030 --> 04:27.397
OKAY.

04:27.430 --> 04:29.864
LET ME KNOW
WHAT YOU FIND.

04:32.840 --> 04:34.796
HEY.

04:34.840 --> 04:35.966
HEY.

04:36.000 --> 04:38.503
WHERE DID YOU GO THIS MORNING?
I DIDN'T HEAR YOU LEAVE.

04:38.540 --> 04:40.371
UH,
EARLY SPIN CLASS.

04:40.410 --> 04:42.037
YOU SHOWERED BEFORE.

04:43.950 --> 04:45.645
THE FLOOR WAS WET.

04:45.680 --> 04:48.319
WOW. YOU SHOULD BE
A DETECTIVE.

04:48.350 --> 04:49.419
WAIT. WAIT.
I DON'T CARE.

04:49.450 --> 04:52.146
IT'S JUST [SIGHS] THINGS
AROUND HERE ARE REALLY WEIRD,

04:52.190 --> 04:55.978
AND...YOU TOOK OFF...
[ SIGHS ]

04:56.020 --> 04:59.399
ARE WE OKAY?

04:59.430 --> 05:02.319
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

05:02.370 --> 05:04.668
I'M INTERNAL AFFAIRS.

05:04.700 --> 05:06.793
YOU'RE WHAT?

05:06.840 --> 05:10.537
LOOK, I WAS ASSIGNED
TO 15 DIVISION AFTER THE BOMBING

05:10.570 --> 05:11.935
TO COLLECT INFORMATION
ON PEOPLE,

05:11.970 --> 05:13.631
AND I-I'M NOT EVEN
SUPPOSED TO BE HERE RIGHT NOW,

05:13.680 --> 05:15.079
BUT I'M JUST WAITING
FOR AN EXIT PLAN.

05:15.110 --> 05:17.249
YOU WERE SPYING ON US?
[ SIGHS ]

05:17.280 --> 05:19.475
I COULDN'T TELL YOU.

05:19.520 --> 05:22.011
SO, WHAT DID YOU TELL THEM?
YOU TELL T'I'VEOM ABOUT US?

05:22.050 --> 05:23.711
DID YOU TELL THEM ABOUT OLIVER?
IS THAT WHY HE'S IN TROUBLE?

05:23.750 --> 05:25.786
NICK...PLEASE.

05:25.820 --> 05:27.356
I NEVER MEANT TO HURT YOU
OR ANYONE,

05:27.390 --> 05:29.483
BUT I --
LOOK, I HAD A JOB TO DO.

05:29.530 --> 05:32.454
AND YOU LANDED ON OLIVER.
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.

05:32.500 --> 05:34.957
YOU FOOLED EVERYONE...
INCLUDING ME.

05:35.000 --> 05:37.594
NICK.

05:40.070 --> 05:41.298
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

05:41.340 --> 05:44.503
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

05:46.040 --> 05:47.871
HEY. I'VE BEEN
LOOKING FOR YOU.

05:47.910 --> 05:49.377
HEY.

05:50.580 --> 05:53.947
WHAT'S WRONG?
NOTHING. WHAT'S UP?

05:53.980 --> 05:55.811
I THINK WE SHOULD TAKE
ANOTHER RUN AT CHRIS KLEM.

05:55.850 --> 05:57.818
[ SIGHS ] REALLY?
YEAH. YEAH.

05:57.850 --> 05:59.283
HOW DO WE KNOW
THAT HE ACTUALLY MET

05:59.320 --> 06:00.480
THE GUY HE THINKS
IS OLIVER SHAW?

06:00.520 --> 06:01.885
HE COULD HAVE
MADE A MISTAKE.

06:01.920 --> 06:03.558
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

06:03.590 --> 06:04.955
THIS WHOLE THING
COULD BE A MISTAKE.

06:04.990 --> 06:07.697
EXACTLY, SO WE SHOULD PROBABLY
GET HIM BACK IN HERE

06:07.730 --> 06:08.958
AND THEN
SHOW HIM SOME PICTURES.

06:09.000 --> 06:10.922
EXCEPT I HANDED HIM OVER
TO I.A. LAST NIGHT.

06:10.970 --> 06:13.029
THEY'RE NOT GONNA LET US
ANYWHERE NEAR HIM.

06:13.070 --> 06:14.662
I'M SORRY.

06:16.640 --> 06:20.178
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

06:20.210 --> 06:21.279
WHERE YOU GOING?

06:21.310 --> 06:23.449
HOMICIDE CALLED --
GUNSHOT VICTIM.

06:23.480 --> 06:25.675
THEY THINK
IT'S GANG-RELATED.

06:27.620 --> 06:30.783
WHY DON'T
I GO WITH YOU?

06:30.820 --> 06:32.458
Steve: HUH? WHY?

06:32.490 --> 06:35.709
I GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE TODAY.
IT'S TOO INTENSE.

06:35.760 --> 06:37.978
I'M THINKING MAYBE
I COULD USE A CHANGE OF SCENE.

06:38.030 --> 06:41.454
WELL [SIGHS]
NOTHING SAYS A CHANGE OF SCENE

06:41.500 --> 06:42.967
LIKE A GANGLAND KILLING.

06:43.000 --> 06:44.524
WHY DON'T YOU SADDLE UP?

06:50.610 --> 06:53.579
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

06:53.610 --> 06:57.774
LOOK AT HIM
STANDING UP THERE.

06:57.810 --> 06:59.539
MAKES ME SICK.

07:03.050 --> 07:04.187
HEY.
HEY.

07:04.220 --> 07:05.448
YOU DOING OKAY?

07:05.490 --> 07:08.015
I KNOW HOW YOU GET EMOTIONAL
AT TIMES LIKE THIS.

07:08.060 --> 07:09.459
I MEAN,
IN A GOOD WAY.

07:09.490 --> 07:11.321
WHY ARE YOU
ASKING ME THAT?

07:11.360 --> 07:14.557
I WAS JUST BEING FRIENDLY.
IS THAT ALLOWED?

07:14.600 --> 07:17.694
UM...I'LL GET BACK
TO YOU.

07:19.100 --> 07:21.864
OKAY,
SETTLE, PEOPLE.

07:21.900 --> 07:25.700
I KNOW YOU'VE ALL HEARD THE NEWS
THAT STAFF SERGEANT OLIVER SHAW

07:25.740 --> 07:26.729
HAS TAKEN A LEAVE OF ABSENCE

07:26.780 --> 07:29.305
PENDING AN I.A. INVESTIGATION
INTO HIS CONDUCT.

07:29.340 --> 07:32.616
FOR THE MOMENT,
THAT'S ALL WE KNOW.

07:32.650 --> 07:34.971
AND THAT'S THE LAST TIME
WE NEED TO DISCUSS IT.

07:35.020 --> 07:36.442
EVERYONE CLEAR ON THAT?

07:36.490 --> 07:37.445
IN THE MEANTIME,

07:37.490 --> 07:39.617
I WILL BE ASSUMING
STAFF SERGEANT SHAW'S DUTIES

07:39.660 --> 07:41.480
UNTIL A SUITABLE REPLACEMENT
CAN BE FOUND.

07:41.520 --> 07:43.056
OR UNTIL
HE'S BEEN CLEARED.

07:43.090 --> 07:45.581
YES,
OR THAT POSSIBILITY.

07:45.630 --> 07:47.598
AND WHILE NO ONE
IS HAPPY ABOUT THIS SITUATION,

07:47.630 --> 07:48.699
WE STILL HAVE A JOB TO DO,

07:48.730 --> 07:51.824
AND I EXPECT YOU ALL
TO REMAIN PROFESSIONAL ABOUT IT.

07:51.870 --> 07:52.894
TO THAT END,

07:52.940 --> 07:55.591
COMMISSIONER SANTANA IS HERE
TO SAY A FEW WORDS.

07:56.910 --> 08:00.471
OKAY,
I WILL BE CONDUCTING A REVIEW

08:00.510 --> 08:03.104
OF ALL CASE FILES
DURING SERGEANT SHAW'S TENURE.

08:03.150 --> 08:05.607
I'M GOING TO NEED
A COUPLE OF VOLUNTEERS.

08:05.650 --> 08:09.040
MCNALLY, EPSTEIN,
YOU'LL DO.

08:09.080 --> 08:10.889
John: THE REST OF YOU, YOUR
ASSIGNMENTS ARE ON THE BOARD.

08:10.920 --> 08:12.239
ANYONE NOT LISTED
IS ON DESK DUTY.

08:12.290 --> 08:14.713
DISMISSED.

08:14.760 --> 08:18.582
EXCEPT YOU, DIAZ.
YOU'RE WITH ME.

08:18.630 --> 08:20.723
WHAT THE HELL
DOES HE WANT WITH ME?

08:20.760 --> 08:23.160
MAYBE IT'S THE FACT
THAT YOU WERE BONING HIS WIFE.

08:23.200 --> 08:24.565
THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

08:24.600 --> 08:26.420
IT'S A LITTLE BIT FUNNY,
DON'T YOU THINK?

08:26.470 --> 08:29.803
[ KNOCK ON WINDOW ]
NOW, DIAZ.

08:29.840 --> 08:32.570
ANDY.

08:34.310 --> 08:36.744
I-I -- I DON'T -- I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN DO THIS, OKAY?

08:36.780 --> 08:38.099
I-I CAN'T JUST
SIT ON MY HANDS

08:38.150 --> 08:40.015
WHILE OLIVER'S
BEING RAKED OVER THE COALS.

08:40.050 --> 08:41.813
WHAT ARE WE SUPPOSED TO DO?
WE ALREADY TRIED TO CLEAR HIM.

08:41.850 --> 08:42.680
IT JUST
MADE THINGS WORSE.

08:42.720 --> 08:44.608
THEN WE TRY
A DIFFERENT TACK, OKAY?

08:44.650 --> 08:45.514
THIS ENTIRE TIME,

08:45.550 --> 08:47.017
WE'VE BEEN SPENDING
ALL OF OUR ENERGY

08:47.060 --> 08:49.210
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHO SANTANA WAS WORKING WITH,

08:49.260 --> 08:51.455
AND WE HAVEN'T EVEN
LOOKED INTO HIM DIRECTLY.

08:51.490 --> 08:53.048
WHAT'S UP?

08:53.100 --> 08:55.455
SORRY. HEY.

08:55.500 --> 08:58.264
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

08:58.300 --> 09:00.689
WHATEVER IT IS,
I'M IN.

09:04.940 --> 09:06.703
ALL RIGHT.

09:06.740 --> 09:09.948
WE THINK COMMISSIONER SANTANA
IS DIRTY.

09:09.980 --> 09:12.676
ALL RIGHT.

09:12.720 --> 09:14.870
HE'S BEEN WORKING WITH SOMEONE
HERE AT 15 DIVISION

09:14.920 --> 09:16.148
TO MAKE IT LOOK
LIKE OLIVER.

09:16.180 --> 09:17.886
BUT IT ISN'T OLIVER,
AND WE NEED TO PROVE IT.

09:17.920 --> 09:19.478
WHERE ARE YOU GUYS
GETTING THIS?

09:19.520 --> 09:22.353
BEFORE TED MCDONALD DIED, HE
TOLD SAM THAT SANTANA WAS DIRTY.

09:22.390 --> 09:25.154
ALL THE PROOF IS ON THOSE HARD
DRIVES IN THE EVIDENCE ROOM.

09:25.190 --> 09:27.351
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
SPYING ON THE COMMISSIONER?

09:27.400 --> 09:29.994
YEAH.

09:30.030 --> 09:31.520
WE GET CAUGHT,
I'LL WEAR IT.

09:31.570 --> 09:35.336
IF I CAN'T CLEAR OLIVER'S NAME,
I DON'T WANT THIS JOB ANWVAY.

09:39.540 --> 09:41.735
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

09:46.450 --> 09:49.339
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

09:49.380 --> 09:50.642
[ SIGHS ]

09:50.690 --> 09:52.578
LOOK, IF YOU'RE WANTING TO, UH,
YELL AT ME FOR SPYING ON YOU,

09:52.620 --> 09:53.587
YOU'RE TOO LATE.

09:53.620 --> 09:54.985
NICK ALREADY
GAVE ME AN EARFUL.

09:55.020 --> 09:57.181
I'M NOT HERE
TO YELL AT YOU.

09:57.230 --> 09:59.186
I NEED YOUR HELP.

09:59.230 --> 10:00.299
OKAY.

10:01.960 --> 10:04.929
I THINK
COMMISSIONER SANTANA

10:04.970 --> 10:06.528
IS THE ONE
WHO ORCHESTRATED THE BOMBING.

10:06.570 --> 10:08.959
THAT'S A DANGEROUS THING
TO SAY.

10:09.000 --> 10:10.638
AM I WRONG?

10:10.670 --> 10:13.935
I KNOW YOU'RE I.A.
YOU'RE HERE FOR SOMETHING.

10:13.980 --> 10:15.732
[ SIGHS ]

10:15.780 --> 10:17.748
OKAY, LOOK,
MY PURPOSE HERE

10:17.780 --> 10:19.600
IS TO FIND OUT
WHO SANTANA WAS WORKING WITH.

10:19.650 --> 10:20.878
I KNEW IT. GREAT.

10:20.920 --> 10:22.717
SO THEN YOU HAVE ACCESS
TO HIS FILES, NO?

10:22.750 --> 10:25.241
HELL, NO.
THAT'S WAY ABOVE MY PAY GRADE.

10:25.290 --> 10:27.781
OKAY. THAN KS.

10:29.290 --> 10:30.450
AN DY.
WHAT?

10:30.490 --> 10:33.254
I MEAN, THERE IS -- THERE'S
SOMETHING THAT WE COULD TRY.

10:33.300 --> 10:34.392
OKAY.

10:34.430 --> 10:36.660
AN INTEGRITY TEST.

10:36.700 --> 10:37.792
WHAT'S THAT?

10:37.830 --> 10:40.162
THEY USE IT ALL THE TIME AT I.A.
IT'S BASICALLY A STING.

10:40.200 --> 10:41.394
YOU PUT THE COMMISSIONER
IN A POSITION

10:41.440 --> 10:44.534
TO OVERHEAR FALSE INFORMATION
THAT MAKES HIM FEEL THREATENED.

10:44.570 --> 10:46.538
AND THEN
YOU SIT AND YOU WAIT.

10:46.570 --> 10:48.208
AND IF
HE TAKES THE BAIT,

10:48.240 --> 10:51.141
THEN YOU CAN CONFIRM
THAT HE'S CORRUPT.

10:51.180 --> 10:52.340
OKAY.

10:52.380 --> 10:54.473
THAT SOUNDS GREAT, EXCEPT
WHAT ARE WE GONNA USE FOR BAIT?

10:54.520 --> 10:57.819
TED MCDONALD'S HARD DRIVES.
THINK ABOUT IT. THEY'RE PERFECT.

10:57.850 --> 10:59.010
YEAH,
THEY'RE PERFECT,

10:59.050 --> 11:01.587
EXCEPT FOR THE FACT THAT THEY
BLEW UP ABOUT FOUR MONTHS AGO.

11:01.620 --> 11:04.657
THE REAL ONES BLEW UP, SURE,
BUT WHOEVER PLANTED THAT BOMB

11:04.690 --> 11:05.884
WAS TERRIFIED
OF WHAT THEY MIGHT CONTAIN.

11:05.930 --> 11:08.194
IMAGINE WHAT THEY'D DO IF A
DUPLICATE SET SUDDENLY APPEARED.

11:08.230 --> 11:10.596
SO,
SANTANA MIGHT PANIC,

11:10.630 --> 11:12.063
AND THAT'LL FORCE HIM
TO PLAY HIS HAND.

11:12.100 --> 11:14.159
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]
Nick: BUT WAIT A SECOND.

11:14.200 --> 11:16.339
HOW DO WE EXPLAIN THAT
A SECOND SET'S JUST SHOWN UP?

11:16.370 --> 11:20.534
WHAT IF A FRIEND OF TED'S HAS,
LIKE, FINALLY COME FORWARD?

11:20.580 --> 11:22.070
YOU KNOW,
TED COULD HAVE SENT HIM

11:22.110 --> 11:24.078
A DUPLICATE SET OF DRIVES
IN THE EVENT OF HIS DEATH.

11:24.110 --> 11:26.408
AND THEN JUST HAVE HIM COME IN,
TELL HIS STORY,

11:26.450 --> 11:28.748
AND THEN
LET SANTANA OVERHEAR.

11:28.780 --> 11:30.441
YEAH, BUT WHO?

11:30.490 --> 11:32.117
I MIGHT HAVE SOMEONE.

11:32.150 --> 11:34.584
IS SANTANA EVEN GONNA BELIEVE
THIS, THOUGH, COMING FROM US?

11:34.620 --> 11:36.588
HOW DO WE GET
THE INFORMATION TO HIM?

11:36.620 --> 11:38.724
[ SIREN CHIRPS ]

11:38.760 --> 11:43.561
TROJAN HORSE.
HE'S STANDING RIGHT THERE.

11:43.600 --> 11:45.591
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

11:45.630 --> 11:49.930
[ SIREN CHIRPING ]

11:49.970 --> 11:50.834
HEY!

11:50.870 --> 11:52.428
TOOK YOU LONG ENOUGH.

11:52.470 --> 11:53.937
IT'S JUST A MURDER,
NO BIG DEAL.

11:53.980 --> 11:55.277
Steve:
YEAH, OBVIOUSLY.

11:55.310 --> 11:56.675
[ CHUCKLES ]
HEY.

11:56.710 --> 11:58.200
DETECTIVE FRANKIE ANDERSON,
HOMICIDE.

11:58.250 --> 11:59.274
HI.
EASY TO REMEMBER

11:59.310 --> 12:00.868
'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT EVERYONE
WANTS TO DO TO HER.

12:00.920 --> 12:03.013
OH, THEY WANT TO HOMICIDE ME.
THAT'S VERY CLEVER.

12:03.050 --> 12:05.245
OKAY. WHAT DO WE GOT?
[ CLAPS HANDS ]

12:05.290 --> 12:06.985
UH, MALE, 30$,
DOUBLE TAP TO THE HEAD,

12:07.020 --> 12:09.250
NO I.D., BUT HE IS A MEMBER
OF THE COBRAS.

12:09.290 --> 12:11.349
CORONER SAID
HE WAS ON HIS KNEES.
ANY LEADS?

12:11.390 --> 12:13.529
WITNESS HEARD SCREAMING
BEFORE THE GUNSHOTS.

12:13.560 --> 12:15.198
SOMEONE YELLED
THE NAME "TROY BAXTER."

12:15.230 --> 12:17.323
IT TURNS OUT HE'S ALSO
A MEMBER OF THE COBRAS.

12:17.370 --> 12:21.397
HE HAS A LONG RAP SHEET FULL OF
ASSAULT CHARGES, NO CONVICT IONS.

12:21.440 --> 12:24.932
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

12:24.970 --> 12:27.177
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

12:34.350 --> 12:36.716
THIS IS OUR BOY.

12:36.750 --> 12:38.741
[ SIGHS ]

12:38.790 --> 12:40.712
WHAT? WHAT WAS THAT?
WHAT'S WRONG?

12:40.760 --> 12:42.489
NOTHING.

12:42.520 --> 12:44.624
NOTHING, MY ASS.
YOU KNOW THIS GUY?

12:44.660 --> 12:46.821
NO, NO, I NEVER
MET HIM BEFORE IN MY LIFE.

12:46.860 --> 12:48.589
I JUST NEED TO,
UH, MAKE CALL.

12:48.630 --> 12:50.598
I'LL MEET YOU OUTSIDE.

12:50.630 --> 12:53.793
CHARMING.
IS HE ALWAYS LIKE THIS?

12:53.840 --> 12:57.867
NO. NO, HE'S NOT.

12:57.910 --> 13:00.128
Andy: ARE YOU NUTS?
THE LAST TIME WE GOT THE --

13:00.180 --> 13:01.477
NO, FORGET IT.
YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

13:01.510 --> 13:03.705
BUT WE DON'T HAVE
ANOTHER CHOICE --
YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?

13:03.750 --> 13:04.978
WE GOT TO FIGURE
SOMETHING ELSE OUT, DON'T WE?

13:05.010 --> 13:07.717
[ SIGHS ] I THINK THAT'S IT.
THAT'S OUT-IEYVLY OPTION.

13:07.750 --> 13:09.980
WHAT, UH -- WHAT --
WHAT YOU TALKING ABOUT?

13:10.020 --> 13:12.443
NOTHING.
ROOKIE,
HOW MUCH OF THAT YOU HEAR?

13:12.490 --> 13:13.718
BARELY ANYTHING.

13:13.760 --> 13:16.581
GOOD.
STAY OUT OF IT.

13:16.620 --> 13:17.985
HEY, COME ON, GUYS,
SERIOUSLY.

13:18.030 --> 13:20.351
TELL ME WHAT YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT. IT SOUNDS CRAZY.

13:20.400 --> 13:22.254
WHAT'S UP?
OKAY, JUST...

13:24.330 --> 13:25.627
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

13:25.670 --> 13:28.833
SAM SAID THAT SOME GUY BY THE
NAME OF KYLE MASON CALLED HIM,

13:28.870 --> 13:29.962
A FRIEND
OF TED MCDONALD'S.

13:30.010 --> 13:32.228
TED MCDONALD?
SHH!

13:32.270 --> 13:34.602
LIKE -- LIKE --
LIKE "KABOOM"?
YEAH.

13:34.640 --> 13:35.868
THAT'S HIM.

13:35.910 --> 13:37.309
THIS GUY KYLE CLAIMS HE HAS
A SECOND SET OF THE HARD DRIVES

13:37.350 --> 13:38.248
THAT WERE DESTROYED
IN THE EXPLOSION.

13:38.280 --> 13:40.248
HE WANTS TO COME IN
AND GIVE A STATEMENT.

13:40.280 --> 13:41.440
NICK'S GONNA PICK HIM UP
IN AN HOUR.

13:43.990 --> 13:45.719
THIS IS A COVERT AFFAIR,
AND YOU'RE IN IT NOW.

13:45.750 --> 13:48.389
COVERT? NO, I KNOW.
I LIKE THAT.

13:48.420 --> 13:50.684
GUYS, LOOK, MY --
MY LIPS ARE SEALED.

13:50.730 --> 13:52.550
ALL RIGHT.
OKAY. GIVE ME THAT.

13:52.590 --> 13:53.989
TEAMWORK, OKAY?
STOP IT.

13:54.030 --> 13:55.349
[ FINGERS SNAP ]

14:00.040 --> 14:02.338
[ INDISTINCT TALKING OVER P.A. ]

14:05.710 --> 14:07.928
HOW LONG
BEFORE HE SPILLS THE BEANS?

14:07.980 --> 14:11.108
[ SCOFFS ]
GIVE IT AN HOUR.

14:21.620 --> 14:24.225
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

14:24.260 --> 14:25.079
John: DIAZ.

14:25.130 --> 14:26.620
I'M STEPPING OUT
FOR AWHILE.

14:26.660 --> 14:27.820
COVER ME
WHILE I'M GONE.

14:27.860 --> 14:30.090
SURE. UH, WHAT SHOULD I SAY
IF ANYONE ASKS?

14:30.130 --> 14:31.324
I DON'T KNOW.
MAKE SOMETHING UP.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.099
I'M PRETTY SURE
YOU CAN HANDLE THAT.

14:36.440 --> 14:40.536
[ GLASSES CLINKING ]

14:40.580 --> 14:43.799
[ TV CHATTER ]

14:43.850 --> 14:45.203
YOU ARE
AN OFFICER OF THE LAW,

14:45.250 --> 14:47.218
AND I AM NO LONGER AN OFFICER
OF THE LAW,

14:47.250 --> 14:49.218
SO WE HAVE NOTHING
TO DISCUSS.

14:51.650 --> 14:56.019
NO. PLENTY OF PLACES TO SIT
THAT AREN'T RIGHT THERE.

14:56.060 --> 14:58.255
[ HORNS HONK IN DISTANCE ]

15:03.000 --> 15:05.218
OLIVER,
I UNDERSTAND YOU'RE UPSET.

15:05.270 --> 15:07.488
"UPSET" IS NOT THE WORD.
WHAT IS THE WORD?

15:07.540 --> 15:11.362
KEVIN, WHAT'S A WORD, UH, THAT
MIGHT DESCRIBE HOW A MAN FEELS

15:11.410 --> 15:14.629
WHEN HE DISCOVERS THAT...
AN ORGANIZATION

15:14.680 --> 15:17.046
THAT HE'S POURED MORE
OF 20 YEARS OF HIS LIFE INTO

15:17.080 --> 15:20.174
TURNS AROUND AND, UH,
THROWS HIM UNDER THE BUS?

15:20.220 --> 15:22.313
"BETRAYED"?
YES, "BETRAYED."

15:22.350 --> 15:23.886
EXACTLY.
YOU'RE A WORDSMITH.

15:23.920 --> 15:24.739
AND THAT WORD
IS EXACTLY WHY

15:24.790 --> 15:26.143
I DON'T WANT TO TALK
TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

15:26.190 --> 15:28.283
KEVIN, I'LL HAVE A SCOTCH,
TOO, PLEASE.

15:28.320 --> 15:30.026
WELL,
FREE COUNTRY, I GUESS.

15:30.060 --> 15:31.618
[ SCOTCH POURING ]

15:35.530 --> 15:37.896
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

15:37.930 --> 15:40.899
UH, JUST THOUGHT
I'D BRING THESE FOR YOU.

15:40.940 --> 15:44.137
UH, JUST PUT THEM
OVER THERE.

15:49.280 --> 15:51.578
WHAT, UH...
WHAT YOU DOING?

15:51.610 --> 15:53.976
WHAT IS IT?
UH, NOTHING.

15:54.020 --> 15:55.976
YOU KNOW,
JUST -- JUST IN A GOOD MOOD.

15:56.020 --> 15:57.647
I FEEL LIKE
THINGS ARE LOOKING UP.

15:57.690 --> 15:58.987
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH? WHAT THINGS?

15:59.020 --> 16:01.056
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I CAN'T TELL YOU THAT,

16:01.090 --> 16:02.318
UH, BECAUSE
I'M SWORN TO SECRECY.

16:02.360 --> 16:03.520
LISTEN --
THAT'S GOOD FOR YOU.

16:03.560 --> 16:05.425
LISTEN, UM, CAN YOU SHUT THE
DOOR ON YOUR WAY OUT, PLEASE?

16:05.460 --> 16:06.586
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
I-I WOULD REALLY LIKE TO,

16:06.630 --> 16:08.621
YOU KNOW, BUT -- BUT I-I SW--
I PROMISED THAT I WOULDN'T.

16:08.660 --> 16:09.649
[ FOLDERS THUD ]

16:12.570 --> 16:14.333
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

16:14.370 --> 16:16.133
I'LL JUST --
I'LL JUST PICK THEM UP.

16:16.170 --> 16:17.967
LISTEN, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

16:18.010 --> 16:19.159
JUST GET OUT.
SEND IN A REAL COP.

16:19.210 --> 16:21.075
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

16:21.110 --> 16:23.647
JUST GET OUT. NOW!

16:26.680 --> 16:30.514
WANT TO KNOW
HOW REAL I AM?

16:30.550 --> 16:33.257
I WAS JUST PULLED
INTO A COVERT OPERATION.

16:33.290 --> 16:36.282
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT,
INVOLVING TED MCDONALD.

16:48.700 --> 16:50.668
NO TURNING BACK NOW.

16:50.710 --> 16:52.632
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

16:58.650 --> 17:00.641
PENNY FOR
YOUR THOUGHTS?

17:00.680 --> 17:01.578
[ SIGHS ]

17:01.620 --> 17:03.349
THE DEAD GUY REMINDED ME
OF SOMEONE I KNEW.

17:03.390 --> 17:04.140
THAT'S ALL.

17:04.190 --> 17:06.818
WHO DID YOU CALL?

17:06.850 --> 17:08.886
WHAT ARE YOU --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:08.920 --> 17:10.649
ARE YOU
CHECKING UP ON ME?

17:13.100 --> 17:15.421
I NEED TO MAKE A STOP.

17:19.570 --> 17:22.334
[ BRAKES SQUEAL ]

17:22.370 --> 17:24.201
[ PARKING BRAKE CLICKS ]

17:24.240 --> 17:26.800
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

17:26.840 --> 17:27.807
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

17:27.840 --> 17:30.070
WHAT'S THIS PLACE?
I WON'T BE LONG.

17:30.110 --> 17:32.374
JUST STAY IN THE CAR, ALL RIGHT?
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

18:02.540 --> 18:05.475
WOMAN: The number you have
dialed is no longer in service.

18:05.510 --> 18:07.444
Please check the number --
[ Click]

18:09.850 --> 18:12.216
[ SIGHS ]
[ CHILDREN PLAYING ]

18:12.250 --> 18:13.956
LOOKING GOOD, NICK.

18:13.990 --> 18:16.481
UNIFORM WORKS.
YOU'RE LATE.

18:16.520 --> 18:18.488
WHAT, FIVE MINUTES?
GIVE ME A BREAK.

18:18.530 --> 18:20.418
IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M DRIVING A MASERATI HERE.

18:20.460 --> 18:22.121
I WAS WORRIED
YOU'D CHICKENED OUT.

18:22.160 --> 18:22.922
[ SCOFFS ]

18:22.960 --> 18:24.928
YOU'VE SEEN
MY APARTMENT, RIGHT?

18:24.970 --> 18:26.790
IT'S GOOD
TO GET OUT OF THERE.

18:26.830 --> 18:27.933
SPEAKING OF WHICH,

18:27.970 --> 18:30.336
WE'RE STILL DOING THAT BALLGAME
ON SATURDAY, RIGHT?

18:30.370 --> 18:32.133
LET'S JUST FOCUS
ON THIS FIRST.

18:32.170 --> 18:33.501
REMEMBER -- YOU AND I
DON'T KNOW EACH OTHER.

18:33.540 --> 18:35.098
YOU JUST STICK TO THE FACTS
WE TALKED ABOUT.

18:35.140 --> 18:37.643
NICK, RELAX.

18:37.680 --> 18:40.478
WHO DO YOU KNOW
THAT'S A BETTER LIAR THAN ME?

18:40.520 --> 18:42.613
OKAY.

18:42.650 --> 18:43.639
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

18:43.690 --> 18:44.440
[ DOOR BEEPS ]

18:44.490 --> 18:45.787
THANK YOU FOR COMING IN,
MR. MASON.

18:45.820 --> 18:47.458
CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?
WATER?

18:47.490 --> 18:48.855
I JUST WANT TO
GET THIS OVER WITH.

18:48.890 --> 18:51.779
OKAY, UH, IT'S STILL GONNA BE
A FEW MORE MINUTES.

18:51.830 --> 18:52.888
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

18:52.930 --> 18:56.024
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:56.060 --> 18:58.528
SIR. CAN I HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING?

18:58.570 --> 19:00.231
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
YEAH, I HEARD
YOU BROUGHT SOMEONE IN

19:00.270 --> 19:01.430
WHO HAS INFORMATION
ON THE EVIDENCE-ROOM BOMBING.

19:01.470 --> 19:03.961
THAT'S RIGHT. OFFICER MCNALLY
JUST WENT TO GET A DETECTIVE.

19:04.010 --> 19:05.261
I THINK
I'LL LISTEN IN.

19:05.310 --> 19:07.232
THIS CASE
HAS SPECIAL MEANING TO ME.

19:07.280 --> 19:08.201
[ DOOR BEEPS ]
I'M SORRY.

19:08.240 --> 19:09.832
THERE ISN'T A DETECTIVE
AVAILABLE RIGHT NOW.

19:09.880 --> 19:10.847
DO YOU MIND WAITING?

19:10.880 --> 19:11.676
OH, COME ON.

19:11.710 --> 19:13.678
I BUSTED MY ASS
TO COME DOWN HERE.

19:13.720 --> 19:15.176
I JUST WANT TO GET THESE THINGS
OUT OF MY LIFE,

19:15.220 --> 19:16.369
AND YOU CAN'T
TAKE MY STATEMENT?

19:16.420 --> 19:17.785
WELL, NO --
I MEAN, IT'S A PIECE OF PAPER.

19:17.820 --> 19:19.640
UH, NO, IT'S OKAY. I CAN
TAKE YOUR STATEMENT. THE --

19:19.690 --> 19:21.112
IT'S A...
PEN AND A TAPE RECORDER.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.583
[ VELCRO TEARS ]

19:23.630 --> 19:25.723
[ SIGHS ]

19:25.760 --> 19:29.252
OKAY, SO...

19:29.300 --> 19:31.268
WHEN DID YOU
FIRST RECEIVE THE HARD DRIVES?

19:31.300 --> 19:32.392
ABOUT SIX MONTHS AGO.

19:32.430 --> 19:33.931
HE SENT THEM
WITH A NOTE THAT SAID

19:33.970 --> 19:37.133
RELEASE THEM TO THE MEDIA
IN THE EVENT OF HIS DEATH.

19:37.170 --> 19:38.068
AND YOU DIDN'T DO THAT.

19:38.110 --> 19:39.168
NO, I DIDN'T KNOW
TED WAS IN TROUBLE.

19:39.210 --> 19:42.008
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW HE DIED
UNTIL A FEW WEEKS AGO.

19:42.040 --> 19:43.541
WHERE ARE
THE HARD DRIVES NOW?

19:43.580 --> 19:46.140
I -- THEY'RE AT WORK.
WHERE'S THAT?

19:46.180 --> 19:48.148
I RENT A SPACE.
IT'S A TOOL-AND-DIE SHOP.

19:48.180 --> 19:49.374
AND WHAT'S
THE ACTUAL ADDRESS?

19:49.420 --> 19:50.785
278 LIBERTY STREET.

19:50.820 --> 19:53.141
WHERE WOULD WE FIND
THE HARD DRIVES?

19:53.190 --> 19:54.953
IN A CABINET
UNDER MY WORKBENCH.

19:54.990 --> 19:57.720
YOU'LL FIND THEM IN THE CORNER,
AGAINST THE SOUTH WALL.

19:57.760 --> 19:58.658
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

19:58.690 --> 20:00.294
A DETECTIVE
WILL PROBABLY REACH OUT TO YOU

20:00.330 --> 20:01.399
IF THEY HAVE
MORE QUESTIONS.

20:01.430 --> 20:03.864
IN THE MEANTIME, I'LL ARRANGE
A RIDE HOME FOR YOU.

20:03.900 --> 20:05.390
OKAY.
THANK YOU.

20:05.430 --> 20:07.261
THANK YOU.
[ DOOR BEEPS ]

20:07.300 --> 20:08.858
SHOULD I SEND A CAR
TO GO PICK THEM UP?

20:08.900 --> 20:10.128
NO.

20:10.170 --> 20:13.139
NO ONE DOES ANYTHING WITH THIS
UNTIL A DETECTIVE REVIEWS IT.

20:13.170 --> 20:15.968
AND KEEP IT TO YOURSELF.
YOU UNDERSTAND?

20:16.010 --> 20:19.104
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

20:19.150 --> 20:20.447
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

20:22.320 --> 20:24.538
SO? DID HE BUY IT?

20:24.590 --> 20:27.889
BETTER CALL
NICK AND GAIL.

20:27.920 --> 20:30.286
ALL RIGHT, SO,
WE'RE HERE NOW.

20:30.330 --> 20:32.924
WE'RE JUST GONNA BE
WAITING INSIDE WHEN HE ARRIVES.

20:37.930 --> 20:40.262
[ LID CREAKS ]

20:43.910 --> 20:46.265
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

20:46.310 --> 20:48.073
I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU
TO STAY IN THE CAR.

20:48.110 --> 20:50.670
THERE'S MAIL IN THAT MAILBOX
ADDRESSED 1YCEAl-HROY BAXT ER...

20:50.710 --> 20:52.575
...AS IN THE SUSPECT
IN OUR MURDER INVESTIGATION.

20:52.610 --> 20:53.975
OUR MURDER
INVESTIGATION?

20:54.020 --> 20:57.148
IS THIS HIS PLACE?
WERE YOU JUST TALKING TO HIM?

20:57.180 --> 20:59.284
JUST LEAVE IT ALONE,
OKAY?

20:59.320 --> 21:01.686
THE HELL I WILL.

21:01.720 --> 21:02.755
LISTEN.

21:02.790 --> 21:04.553
LISTEN. LISTEN!

21:04.590 --> 21:08.424
LISTEN, YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE, ALL RIGHT?

21:08.460 --> 21:10.291
JUST --
SO EXPLAIN IT, THEN.

21:10.330 --> 21:12.696
[ KEYS JINGLING ]
[ SIGHS ]

21:12.730 --> 21:16.439
JUST GET BACK IN THE CAR.
PLEASE GET BACK IN THE CAR.

21:16.470 --> 21:18.404
I'LL MEET YOU
AT THE STATION.

21:27.580 --> 21:29.548
FINE. SAY WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA SAY.

21:29.580 --> 21:30.945
RIGHT. YOU COULDN'T
JUST LOOP ME IN.

21:30.990 --> 21:33.686
YOU COULDN'T
PUT ME IN THE LOOP.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

21:33.720 --> 21:36.553
IT'S NOT -- I-I DIDN'T HAVE TIME
TO DO ANY OF THAT STUFF, OKAY?

21:36.590 --> 21:38.319
THERE WAS NO TIME
TO LOOP YOU IN.

21:38.360 --> 21:42.228
HERE'S THE DEAL. HERE'S WHAT
YOU NEED TO KNOW, OKAY?

21:42.260 --> 21:44.490
AFTER THE EXPLOSION
IN THE EVIDENCE ROOM,

21:44.530 --> 21:48.489
I ASKED NOELLE
TO INITIATE AN INVESTIGATION

21:48.540 --> 21:50.508
INTO
COMMISSIONER SANTANA.

21:50.540 --> 21:54.670
OLIVER, I'M SORRY TO TELL YOU
THIS, BUT YOUR EX-T.O. IS DIRTY.

21:54.710 --> 21:56.769
HE'S AS DIRTY
AS THEY COME.

21:56.810 --> 21:58.846
HE'S THE REASON
YOU'RE SITTING ON THAT STOOL.

21:58.880 --> 22:01.849
HE'S BEHIND
ALL OF THIS.

22:01.880 --> 22:04.041
YOU DON'T LOOK
VERY SURPRISED BY THAT.

22:04.090 --> 22:05.785
YEAH,
I'M NOT VERY SURPRISED.

22:05.820 --> 22:08.516
SANTANA PAID ME
A LITTLE VISIT THIS MORNING,

22:08.560 --> 22:11.654
BRIGHT AND EARLY
ON MY DECK.

22:11.690 --> 22:14.727
OFFERED ME A BIG JOB
IN THE PRIVATE SECTOR,

22:14.760 --> 22:17.558
A COMPANY CALLED
BLAND-TECH SOMETHING.

22:17.600 --> 22:18.862
[ BREATH ES DEEPLY ]

22:18.900 --> 22:21.596
NOW, THAT'S A COINCIDENCE,
HMM? HUH?

22:21.640 --> 22:23.460
AND WHAT HAPPENS
TO THE INVESTIGATION?

22:23.510 --> 22:26.468
THERE WILL NOT BE
AN INVESTIGATION.

22:26.510 --> 22:29.399
THAT'S WHAT WILL HAPPEN
WITH THAT.

22:29.440 --> 22:34.412
I STAY QUIT,
AND I RETIRE FROM THE FORCE.

22:34.450 --> 22:38.819
SO HE WANTS TO BUY YOU OFF.
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

22:43.490 --> 22:46.653
I-I KNOW
HOW THIS IS GONNA PLAY OUT.

22:46.690 --> 22:49.989
I GIVE MYSELF MAYBE A MONTH,
YOU KNOW,

22:50.030 --> 22:53.466
BEFORE MY, UH -- BEFORE MY UNION
LAWYER BACKS OUT OF THIS THING,

22:53.500 --> 22:55.331
YOU KNOW, CITES A CONFLICT
OF INTEREST OR SOMETHING,

22:55.370 --> 22:57.861
SO I GOT TO -- WHAT? --
SELL THE CABIN, YOU KNOW,

22:57.910 --> 23:00.299
TRIPLE-MORTGAGE MY HOUSE
JUST SO I CAN, UH --

23:00.340 --> 23:02.501
SO I CAN HIRE MY OWN LAWYER
AND FIGHT THIS

23:02.540 --> 23:04.508
AND -- AND --
AND EVENTUALLY PLEA DOWN

23:04.550 --> 23:08.247
TO A -- A LESS HUMILIATING
BUT CAREER-ENDING CHARGE?

23:08.280 --> 23:11.909
OR THE FLIP
IS BLAND-TECH.

23:11.950 --> 23:13.918
YOU KNOW, I'M HOME
BY 6:00 EVERY NIGHT,

23:13.960 --> 23:16.281
YOU KNOW, FOUR WEEKS VACATION,
LOTS OF DOUGH.

23:16.320 --> 23:19.881
CLEAR. LOOKS CLEAR.

23:19.930 --> 23:21.659
[ SNIFFS ]

23:25.030 --> 23:27.260
THIS MIGHT BE IT.

23:27.300 --> 23:28.858
STAY WITH HIM.

23:28.900 --> 23:31.835
SEE WHERE HE GOES.

23:45.290 --> 23:48.259
MCNALLY.
YOU LOOKING FOR SOMEONE?

23:48.290 --> 23:51.657
YOU, ACTUALLY.

23:51.690 --> 23:53.499
I DIDN'T KNOW IF YOU WANTED ME
TO PULL SOME MORE CASE FILES.

23:53.530 --> 23:55.794
NOT AT THE MOMENT.

23:55.830 --> 23:57.695
I'LL LET YOU KNOW.
OF COURSE.

